sections.text:
No writ of error or writ of certiorari issuing from the Supreme Court in any criminal cause shall operate as a stay of execution of the sentence of the trial court unless such writ of error or writ of certiorari be sued out within 30 day
§

 4847B;35 Del. Laws, c. 231; 

Code 1935,

§

 5327; 

11 Del. C. 1953,

§

 4502;
